Array of eight surface barrier detectors
separated by 5 degree,  which can be moved to cover
170 degree.  An additional surface barrier detector
placed at a fixed angle of  15.0+/-0.1 or 23.0+/-0.1
degree was used for normalization.  A Faraday Cup at
the end of the beam line was used to monitor and to
integrate the total charge of the beam; in addition
it was used to carry out  absolute normalization.
The total uncertainties of the cross
sections ranged from 1% to 15%,  except for those
measured at E-CM >18 MeV for 6Li and E-CM >17.5 MeV
for 7Li,  where the uncertainties reached values of
25% at the most backward angles.

Additional details about the  detector system and the

Targets of enriched (99.8%)
selenium-80, 110  mu-g/cm2 thick, evaporated on
20 mu-g/cm2 thick carbon foils,  were placed at the
center of a 80-cm-diameter scattering chamber.
